We know that flavor and aroma are defined by little molecules generated from chemical reactions, prior to or during the cooking Our process begins with the identification ofsome of the key proteins participating in the generation of flavors, aroma, color, and texture of animal origin These are myoglobin and Myoglobin is the protein that gives red color to meet and also participates in the formation of the flavor and aroma that we associate with roast Casein , on the other hand, are a family of proteins present in milk, and they play a fundamental role in the texture and flavors of fermented dairy products like cheese and STEP TWO So, how we produce these proteins without using animals? The answer CARROTS! Thanks to biotechnology advances, our scientists have developed a process under the highest safety and quality standards, from carrot cell They are not only able to express myoglobin and casein exceptionally but also, they give our products an additional plus of nutrients, such as making food not only healthy and nutritious but delicious! STEP THREE In the case you are Yes, this is an process, from the start to To produce foods from myoglobin or caseins, we need to obtain them on a large For this we have developed a platform known as Plant Cell Culture in Suspension (CCVS). This platform allows us to introduce small amounts of our cells into bioreactors and induce their reproduction under controlled conditions, obtaining industrial Then the cells are purified under the most rigorous All this, without resorting to animal husbandry, excessive use of water, soil and very inferior harmful emissions of gases that contribute to the greenhouse STEP FOUR VOILA! Time to create delicious foods The proteins obtained in large volumes are finally mixed with other vegetable ingredients such as soy proteins, pea proteins, coconut oil, fibers, and This is how we finally create delicious foods, with an indistinguishable taste and extraordinarily similar to an animal derived, and in an Sustainability in the smartest way Changing the way we grow, make, consume and waste is a big way we can make an impact We reduce the CO 2 footprint Creating food from biotechnological processes is one of our main This implies a significant reduction in the emission of greenhouse gases and energy We protect animals life Ergo is breaking with old paradigms by developing an alternative and scalable protein production process without resorting to animals as a We reduce water consumption Our technological platform allows us to reduce up to thousand times the consumption of water required to produce standard foods of this Whereas it takes between and liters of water During the recruiting process, Erin kept hitting dead ends, and every piece of advice she was offered get seemed to be meant for someone who looked quite different from Eventually, Erin successfully made her career transition into But the obstacle course that she had to complete to get there? Edit this page on GitHub   Features - Dendron Link Search Menu Expand Document üå± with üíï using Dendron üå≤ Dendron Features Features Hierarchies Dendron proposes hierarchies as the human solution to information This is because there are few things as effective as a hiearchy for quickly filtering an overwhelming amount of information to something humans can work You can read this blog post for the extended rationale behind In Dendron, you can quickly lookup related notes by their Hierarchies are simply . delimited filenames, similar to the hierarchies made by domain names (eg. ). The following are a few notes that have this hierarchical naming - - - - Lookup Lookup is the process of finding a note by traversing its Lookups are quick What s nice about using the . delimited format is that a note can be both a file (something that contains data) and a folder (something that contains other files) at the same time . You can be a file and have your folder too Dendron uses fuzzy matching on paths so you don t have to type out the whole Lazyness is the key to success You can use lookup to figure out what is true! Schemas If you re paying close attention, you might have noticed some icons popup during These icons indicate the schema associated with the Think of schemas as an optional type system for your They describe the hierarchy of your notes and are themselves, represented as a You can create a schema by adding a YAML file with the following naming scheme name .schema.yml to your Below is an example of a hierarchy describing cli You don t need to concern yourself with the details of the schema syntax just yet, just know that this schema will match the following glob patterns : , .cmd , .cmd. , .env - id : cli desc : command line interface reference parent : root namespace : true children : - cmd - env - id : env desc : variables relevant for command - id : cmd desc : subcommands namespace : true Schemas help you organize your notes by letting you know what comes The + sign next to the suggestion indicates that the note does not exist but is part of the Schema suggestions don t show you an endless lineup of tags or folders - they only show you suggestions scoped to your specific level of the hierarchy that you are looking The nice thing about these suggestions is that you can also ignore Sometimes rules schemas are meant to be broken Dendron will show you a ? next to the result in future results but otherwise will assume that you know VS Code Dendron is built on top of VSCode, the IDE from Dendron runs as a plugin inside If you use VSCode today, it means that all your current knowledge, settings and extensions will carry over into If you don t, no sweat, because Dendron will create an optimal workspace with recommended settings and extensions when you first launch Recommended Extensions Since Dendron runs on top of VSCode, it means that you also have access to thousands of extensions to customize Dendron exactly how you like By default, Dendron will initialize your first workspace with the following extensions and Markdown Notes wiki links tags backlinks (think Roam) Markdown Sho

By Charles Anselm April , No Comments Photo by Tim Mossholder on Unsplash ‚ÄúWhat‚Äôs in a name? That which we call a rose by any other name would smell as ‚Äù ‚Äì Juliet, in Shakespeare‚Äôs Romeo and Juliet, declares her love for Romeo and says she loves the person who is actually wearing the ‚ÄúMontague‚Äù name, and not the name itself, or the family it comes Perhaps true, for a rose or a But what about an idea or a movement or a business that is new or Does a name matter? That which we call something conveys a deeper truth about what something Osyte [O-Sight] is an investment technology company founded by a team of portfolio managers, quantitative researchers, traders, asset allocators and enterprise technology We have created a single unified investment technology solution where CIOs, OCIOs and investors can manage their portfolio data, make investment decisions and implement those decisions in a A single system for Data, Decision and Implementation that combines , data science, machine learning and human That‚Äôs a mouthful of an elevator pitch!. What we really do is help investors provide better OVERSIGHT of their public and private market The name Osyte [O-Sight] is another form of the word oversight ‚Äì investment oversight to be We could have just used the name ‚Äòoversight‚Äô but what self respecting silicon valley VC would want to talk to us if we had such a simple We are not ‚Äòkool‚Äô if we don‚Äôt have an unnecessary ‚Äòy‚Äô in the name and cause Make people scratch their heads about how to pronounce that One of the vendors who was trying to get my attention kept saying ‚ÄòOi-stee‚Äô. I didn‚Äôt correct him and say it is pronounced ‚ÄòO-Sight‚Äô. When I did a google search for the name ‚Äòosyte‚Äô to see if anybody else was using it, Google asked me if I meant to search for ‚Äòoyster‚Äô. Google may not be Google if they had just used the name ‚ÄòSearch‚Äô, and ‚Äògoogle‚Äô wouldn‚Äôt be a verb So what‚Äôs in a name? A lot more than we We are investment How do you Osyte? Every living mammal has a physiological system called the Endocannabinoid System (ECS). This regulatory system naturally produces structures throughout the body that foster cellular balance throughout many of your body‚Äôs biological The job of the ECS is to create It produces cannabinoids when the body senses imbalance to help regulate your body to live comfortably, controlling things like pain, sleep, mood, It helps the body‚Äôs neurons navigate the neurotransmitters to the right receiver by elevating levels that are too low or decreasing levels of a hormone that is The ECS has two receptors for cannabinoids called CB1 receptors and CB2 receptors, which are present throughout the CB1 receptors are more prevalent in the brain and deal with coordination and movement, pain, sleep, emotions, mood, thinking, appetite, memory and other CB2 receptors are more common in the immune system and affect inflammation and CBD is a phytocannabinoid (plant-based cannabinoid) that attaches to ECS receptors and inhibits the enzymes that break down endocannabinoids, leading to an increase in the body‚Äôs naturally produced CBD becomes an asset when the body cannot produce enough cannabinoids What are cannabinoids? Cannabinoids are compounds that activate receptors in the body‚Äôs Endocannabinoid System (ECS). developing novel precision medicines targeting driver mutations in oncology, today announced the appointment of Diana Hausman, , as Chief Medical In this role, Hausman will be responsible for leading clinical development and strategy for the ‚ÄúDiana brings invaluable experience and expertise to our team, as we advance our pipeline of precision therapeutics for cancers,‚Äù said Helen Jenkins, Chief Executive Officer, Lengo ‚ÄúHer experience leading several clinical programs in oncology from first in human through to registrational studies is incredibly relevant, as we prepare for our next stage of ‚Äù ‚ÄúI am excited to join the incredible team at Lengo, and work alongside a team of scientists and leaders in kinase inhibition developing transformative therapeutics in oncology,‚Äù said ‚ÄúI look forward to leveraging my extensive clinical experience in the biotechnology industry to lead the continued development of Lengo‚Äôs pipeline for cancer patients with unmet medical ‚Äù Diana Hausman is a medical oncologist with over years of clinical drug development Prior to joining Lengo, she served as Chief Medical Officer for Zymeworks for 5 While at Zymeworks, Hausman oversaw all aspects of clinical development, including advancement of the biparatopic antibody zanidatamab from initial IND to ongoing global Phase 2 and pivotal studies, including breakthrough therapy designation for biliary tract Hausman was previously CMO at Oncothyreon Inc where she oversaw the Phase and early Phase 2 clinical program for the small molecule, She has also held positions of increasing responsibility at ZymoGenetics, Berlex, and Immunex, working across multiple indications, including oncology, hematology, hepatitis C and autoimmune Hausman received her internal medicine
